Packaging type segmentation plays a vital role in shaping the dynamics of the pharmaceutical contract packaging market. Plastic bottles are expected to maintain their dominance due to their cost-effectiveness and widespread use in drug packaging. Blister packaging is gaining traction for its convenience and protective properties against external elements, catering to the demand for efficient and secure packaging solutions. Pouches, known for their flexibility and sustainability attributes, are becoming increasingly popular as pharmaceutical companies seek eco-friendly packaging alternatives.

